723699f-a.title: Manhattan: Vandam Street - Varick Street
723699f-a.text:
Vandam Street, east from No. 32, south side, and No. 31, north
side, east of Varick Street.
May 19, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

723697f-a.title: Manhattan: Vandam Street - Varick Street
723697f-a.text:
21-11 Vandam Street, north side, between Varick Street and
Sixth Avenue (MacDougal Street). Nos. 19 and 17 are old frame
houses faced with brick. The third frame house, No. 15, has been
rebuilt as an all-bruck clubhouse (with the white front and round-
arch doorway).
1932.
.J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 583.
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE ON ALL REPRODUCTIONS.

723757f-a.title: Manhattan: Varick Street - Vandam Street
723757f-a.text:
Varick Street, east side, north from between Vandam and Charlton
Streets, showing the new Graphic Arts Center Building in the block
from King to Houston Streets.
February 12, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
